{{Infobox language |name=Barein |states=[[Chad]] |region=south central |speakers=4,100 |date=1993 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Chadic languages|Chadic]] |fam3=[[East Chadic languages|East Chadic]] |fam4=[[East Chadic B languages|East Chadic B]] |fam5=[[Sokoro languages|Sokoro]] (B.3) |iso3=bva |glotto=bare1279 |glottorefname=Barein }}
'''Barein''' (also known as Baraïn, Barayin, Giulia, Jalkia) is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in south central [[Chad]]. Dialects are Giulia, Jalkia, Komi, and Sakaya.<ref name=e18/>
