{{Infobox language |name=Shebaya |nativename= |region= |states=[[Trinidad]] |extinct=before the 20th century<ref name="google">{{cite book|title=Language Contact in Amazonia|author=Aĭkhenvalʹd, A.I.U.|date=2002|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=9780199257850|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zrUe5BBAIJQC|page=284|accessdate=2015-04-10}}</ref> |ref = |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Maipurean languages|Arawakan]] |fam2 = Northern |fam3 = [[Ta-Arawakan]] |iso3=none |glotto=none |linglist=qk3 }}
'''Shebaya''' (Shebaye, Shebayo) is an extinct [[Arawakan language]] of [[Trinidad]] and perhaps the Venezuelan coast. It is only attested by a few words. Aikhenvald (1999) classifies it with the [[Caribbean Arawakan languages]].
